, 3 regions</td>\r\n            <td>165 MB per day</td>\r\n            <td>1/24 (A core for max 60 min / day)</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Google</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <a href = \"https://cloud.google.com/appengine/\">\r\n                <img style = \"width: 70px\"\r\n                     src = \"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-shlkF4-lOrI/UqEk25whCBI/AAAAAAAAAV4/vAwo6UN2Sis/s1600/appengine_final.png\"/>\r\n                </a>\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>Python, Java, PHP, Go</td>\r\n            <td>MySQL, Google NoSQL Datastore</td>\r\n            <td>Git, Jenkins, IDE SDKs</td>\r\n            <td></td>\r\n\r\n            <td>Unlimited</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <span>1GB Disk</span>,\r\n                <span>1GB Database</span>,\r\n                <span> 5GB\r\n                    <a href = \"https://cloud.google.com/appengine/docs/quotas?hl=en#Default_Gcs_Bucket\">\r\n                        Bucket\r\n                    </a>\r\n                </span>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td>Unlimited</td>\r\n            <td>1GB Outgoing + 1GB Incoming / Day</td>\r\n            <td>28/24 (28 instance hours)</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>SAP</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <a href = \"http://hcp.sap.com/index.html\">\r\n                    <img style = \"width: 70px\"\r\n                         src = \"http://macromicro.com/wp-content/themes/macromicro/assets/img/news/saphana.png\" />\r\n                </a>\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>Java (EE)</td>\r\n            <td>SAP HANA, SAP ASE</td>\r\n            <td>-</td>\r\n            <td><a href = \"https://hcp.sap.com/capabilities.html\">\r\n                Free add-on list</a></td>\r\n\r\n\r\n            <td>1</td>\r\n            <td>1GB Disk, 1GB RDBMS, 1GB Hana</td>\r\n            <td>2GB</td>\r\n            <td>10GB</td>\r\n            <td>1 Core</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>IBM</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <a href = \"http://www.ibm.com/cloud-computing/bluemix/\">\r\n                <img style = \"width: 70px\"\r\n                     src = \"http://www.dbtekpro.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/bluemix-logo.png\"/>\r\n                </a>\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>Java, Node.js, Go, PHP, Python, Ruby, .NET (Mono)</td>\r\n            <td>Mongo, MySQL, PostreSQL, IBM XPages, Redis</td>\r\n            <td>Git, Cloud Foundry</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <a href = \"https://console.ng.bluemix.net/catalog/\">\r\n                    Free add-on list\r\n                </a>\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>Unlimited</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                2GB per App\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td>512MB</td>\r\n            <td>Unlimited</td>\r\n            <td>Unlimited</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Nitrous</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <a href = \"https://www.nitrous.io/\">\r\n                <img style = \"width: 70px\"\r\n                     src = \"https://datafox-data.s3.amazonaws.com/images/cb_f4c94c311b812aa20628f1c32ba52c88.png\"/>\r\n                </a>\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>Ruby, Python, Node.js, PHP, Go, Java, (Extensible)</td>\r\n            <td>Custom (Docker Based)</td>\r\n            <td>Docker, SSH</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                Custom (Docker Based)\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>1</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                1GB\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td>5GB</td>\r\n            <td>Unlimited</td>\r\n            <td>1 Core</td>\r\n\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>App Harbor</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <a href = \"https://appharbor.com/\">\r\n                    <img style = \"width: 70px\"\r\n                         src = \"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1692129271/appharbor-logo_400x400.png\"/>\r\n                </a>\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>.NET</td>\r\n            <td>PostgreSQL, MySQL, Redis, MongoDB</td>\r\n            <td>Git, Mercurial, Subversion, Team Foundation Server</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <a href = \"https://appharbor.com/addons\">Free add-on list</a>\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>1</td>\r\n            <td>Unlimited Disk, 20MB Postgre, 20MB MySQL, 30MB Redis</td>\r\n            <td>512 MB</td>\r\n            <td>100GB/month</td>\r\n            <td>1 Core(~600MHz)</td>\r\n\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Cloudcontrol</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n                <a href = \"https://www.cloudcontrol.com\">\r\n                    <img style = \"width: 70px\"\r\n                         src = \"http://blog.quotaguard.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/cloudcontrollogo.png\" />\r\n                </a>\r\n            </td>\r\n\r\n            <td>Java, Ruby, PHP, Python, (Extensible)</td>\r\n            <td>PostgreSQL, Redis, MongoDB, MySQL</td>\r\n            <td>Git, Bazaar, CLI</td>\r\n            <td><a href = \"https://www.cloudcontrol.com/add-ons\">\r\n                Free add-on list</a></td>\r\n\r\n\r\n            <td>1</td>\r\n            <td>200MB Disk, 20MB Postgre, 496MB MongoDB</td>\r\n            <td>128MB</td>\r\n            <td>Unlimited</td>\r\n            <td>1 Core</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </table>\r\n\r\n    <h4>Notes:</h4>\r\n    <p>\r\n        Almost all of the platforms can scale freely. Most of the platform scale painlessly. It works\r\n        by adding a new CPU core, running a copy of the application, with a load balancing server that automatically\r\n        distributes the request between the application instances.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Almost all platforms have a terrible initial response time. In the free tier, your application is\r\n        swaped out of memory after some n minutes of inactivity. That means that the first user in every n-minute\r\n        time interval needs to wait for the application to be loaded into memory. If the PaaS is runnins SSD's,\r\n        i've measured the delay to be around 1.5s. The worst performer is\r\n        <a href = \"https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/?b=16.33\">Microsoft Azure</a>, where I measure an average of 4s delay.\r\n        The best performer goes to <a href = \"https://console.ng.bluemix.net/\">IBM's Bluemix</a> with 0s delay.\r\n        Bluemix is running on Cloud Foundry, which seems to not swap out processes at all.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        In rare cases (Azure) applications don't allow for own domains.\r\n    </p>"}
